  sub="The rules that keep Krenla worth being part of."
  description="Krenla's community guidelines — what's allowed, what isn't, and how enforcement works."
>
  <div class="prose">
    <p class="updated">Last updated: June 1, 2025</p>

    <div class="note">
      These guidelines apply to all users and all communities on Krenla. Community owners may set stricter rules for their own spaces on top of these.
    </div>

    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <p>Be a decent person. Don't hurt people. Don't post illegal content. Don't spam. Everything else flows from that.</p>

    <h2>What's never allowed</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Child sexual abuse material (CSAM).</strong> Zero tolerance. Immediate account termination and report to authorities.</li>
      <li><strong>Credible threats of violence</strong> against specific individuals or groups.</li>
      <li><strong>Coordinated harassment campaigns</strong> targeting individuals.</li>
      <li><strong>Non-consensual intimate imagery</strong> — sharing explicit images of someone without their consent.</li>
      <li><strong>Doxxing</strong> — publishing private personal information (address, phone number, workplace) to facilitate harm.</li>
      <li><strong>Illegal content</strong> under applicable law, including content that facilitates serious crimes.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we strongly discourage</h2>
    <p>These things aren't always ban-worthy, but they degrade communities and will result in warnings, content removal, or escalating action:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Sustained bad-faith engagement — arguing to exhaust, not to understand</li>
      <li>Spam and repetitive unsolicited promotion</li>
      <li>Impersonating other people or organizations</li>
      <li>Deliberately spreading verifiable misinformation</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Community owner responsibilities</h2>
    <p>If you run a community on Krenla, you're responsible for moderating it in line with these guidelines. Communities that consistently host content violating these rules — even if individual posts are removed — may be suspended.</p>
    <p>Krenla provides community owners with moderation tools, an audit log, and, for larger communities, access to our trust and safety team.</p>

    <h2>How enforcement works</h2>
    <p>Our trust and safety team reviews reports. For most violations, we warn before suspending. For serious violations (CSAM, credible threats), we act immediately.</p>
    <p>Enforcement decisions can be appealed by emailing <a href="mailto:appeals@krenla.com">appeals@krenla.com</a> with your account details and the reason for appeal. We review all appeals within 5 business days.</p>

    <h2>Reporting</h2>
    <p>Every message, thread, and profile on Krenla has a report button. Reports go directly to our trust and safety team. You can also email <a href="mailto:safety@krenla.com">safety@krenla.com</a> for urgent matters.</p>
  </div>
</Page>
